    "# Illustration of importance sampling for GHZ states\n",
    "\n",
    "The script [PurityImportanceSampling](PurityImportanceSampling.py) shows how to access the purity $p_2=\\mathrm{Tr}(\\rho^2)$ based on importance sampling of randomized Measurements [link to the paper](https://arxiv.org/pdf/2102.13524.pdf). \n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "### Description of the experimental situation\n",
    "In this example we consider an experiment where we would like to implement a large $N$-qubit GHZ state\n",
    "\\begin{equation}\n",
    "|\\mathrm{GHZ}\\rangle = \\frac{1}{\\sqrt{2}}\\left(|0\\dots 0\\rangle + |1\\dots 1\\rangle \\right)\n",
    "\\end{equation}\n",
    "However, due to decoherence, we realize instead a mixed-state of the form\n",
    "\\begin{equation}\n",
    "\\rho = (1-p)|\\mathrm{GHZ}\\rangle \\langle \\mathrm{GHZ}| + p \\mathbb{1}/2^N\n",
    "\\end{equation}\n",
    "We would like here to measure the purity $p_2$ of the state $\\rho$. \n",
    "\n",
    "### Measurement protocol with importance sampling of randomized measurements\n",
    "The script is based on randomized measurements. The purity can be expressed as an average over randomized measurements\n",
    "\\begin{equation}\n",
    "p_2=\\int X(u) du \\quad \\mathrm{with}  \\quad X(u) = 2^N\\sum_{s,s'} (-2)^{-D[s,s']} P_u(s) P_u(s')\n",
    "\\end{equation}\n",
    "with $P_u(s)=\\langle s |u \\rho u^\\dagger |s \\rangle$ measurements in the computational basis.  Each CUE local random unitary  $u = \\otimes_i u_i = \\otimes_i R_y(\\theta_i)R_z(\\phi_i)$ is made of single qubit gates.\n",
    "\n",
    "In order to reduce the required number of measuremens, we can use importance sampling and sample unitaries non-uniformly. As we know that the state $\\rho$ is closed to the pure state state $|\\mathrm{GHZ}\\rangle$, which was targeted, we can define a probability distribution\n",
    "\\begin{equation}\n",
    "p_\\mathrm{IS}(u) = \\frac{|X_\\mathrm{GHZ}(u)|}{\\int |X_\\mathrm{GHZ}(u)|} du \\quad \\mathrm{with} \n",
    "\\quad\n",
    "X_\\mathrm{GHZ}(u)=2^N\\sum_{s,s'} (-2)^{-D[s,s']} P^{\\mathrm{GHZ}}_u(s) P^\\mathrm{GHZ}_u(s')\n",
    "\\end{equation}\n",
